# StreamBox Privacy Policy

**Last updated:** 16 July 2026  
**App:** StreamBox (`com.alicious.streambox`)  
**Contact:** alicious.apps@gmail.com

## Summary

StreamBox is a playlist / media player. You add your own M3U URLs or XTREAM credentials.  
StreamBox does **not** host, sell, or provide media content.

## Data we store on your device

- Playlist names and source metadata (M3U URL or XTREAM server / username / password)
- Channel lists, categories, and favorites
- Onboarding completion flag

This data stays on your device unless you back up the device with your OS vendor.

## Analytics & crash reporting

When Firebase is configured for a build:

- **Firebase Analytics** — anonymous event names (e.g. playlist added, channel played). No credentials or stream URLs.
- **Firebase Crashlytics** — anonymous crash stack traces to improve stability.

Until Firebase config files are added, events are logged locally only.

## Network

The app contacts:

- M3U playlist URLs you enter
- XTREAM panel servers you enter
- Stream media URLs from those playlists
- Google Firebase endpoints (when Analytics / Crashlytics are enabled)

Those third parties process data under their own policies.

## Permissions

- **Internet** — to download playlists and play streams

## Your choices

- Delete playlists / favorites in the app
- Uninstall the app to remove local data

## Children’s privacy

StreamBox is not directed at children under 13.

## Changes

We may update this policy. Material changes will be reflected by bumping the “Last updated” date and in-app notice when required.

